<Paragraph>
Bulleted or numbered lists make documents more readable and visually attracted. Many documents - minutes, reading lists, theses, etc. - require numbered or bulleted lists.
</Paragraph>

<Paragraph>
In Microsoft Word, you can add bulleted or numbered lists by selecting the command, Bullets and Numbering, from the Format menu. 
</Paragraph>

<Paragraph>
This sample demonstrates how bulleted or numbered lists can be inserted into a document and how list styles and levels can be applied using Essential DocIO.
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph>
Below is the illustration of the output document.
</Paragraph>
